  "title": "Japanese Historical Eras with Year Ranges",
  "purpose": "Standard taxonomic reference for Japanese history. Used for (1) entity meta-tag validation (e.g. era=heian), (2) discovery views (list entities by era), and (3) cross-cultural temporal synchronization (year ranges in CE/BCE allow alignment with concurrent world history — e.g. mapping Heian Period (794-1185) onto European Early-to-High Medieval Period).",
  "year_system": {
    "convention": "Gregorian-equivalent CE/BCE (negative integers represent BCE)",
    "precision_note": "Era boundaries before 538 CE (introduction of Buddhism) are archaeological estimates and vary by scholar. Modern era boundaries (Meiji onward) are precise to the day in the original Japanese imperial system (元号), but here we use whole-year approximations."
  },
  "license": "CC BY 4.0 (this compilation); underlying periodization is standard scholarly convention",
